# plot the probability density function for a mixture of two Gaussian distributions
means = [1, 2]
variances = [.05, .05]
proportions = [.7, .3]
x = linspace(0, 3, 3000)
y = proportions[0] * norm.pdf(x, loc=means[0], scale=sqrt(variances[0])) +\
    proportions[1] * norm.pdf(x, loc=means[1], scale=sqrt(variances[1]))
figure(figsize=(20,8))
title('Mixture of 2 Gaussians with means = ' + str(means) + ' , variances = ' + str(variances)+ ' and proportions = ' + str(proportions),size=18)
plot(x, y);

In [19]:
# generate a sample
mu=50
std=5
sample = normal(loc=mu, scale=std,size=100)

# calculate parameters
sample_mean = np.mean(sample)
sample_std = np.std(sample)
print('Mean=%.3f, Standard Deviation=%.3f' % (sample_mean, sample_std))

# define the distribution
dist = norm(sample_mean, sample_std)

# sample probabilities for a range of outcomes
values = [value for value in range(mu-4*std, mu+4*std)]
probabilities = [dist.pdf(value) for value in values]

# plot 
fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(22, 10))
fig.subplots_adjust(left=0.0625, right=0.95, wspace=0.1,hspace=0.2)

for axi,b in zip(ax,[[1,5],[10,20]]):
    for axii,bi in zip(axi,b):
        axii.hist(sample, bins=bi,density=True)
        axii.plot(values, probabilities)
        axii.set_title('bins = {}'.format(bi), size=24)

distribution = norm()  # Create normal distribution
data = distribution.rvs(50)  # Draw  random samples

x = np.linspace(np.min(data) - 1, np.max(data) + 1, num=2**10)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(22, 10))
fig.subplots_adjust(left=0.0625, right=0.95, wspace=0.1,hspace=0.2)

for axi,b in zip(ax,[[1,5],[10,20]]):
    for axii,bi in zip(axi,b):
        axii.hist(data, bins=bi,density=True, label='Histogram', edgecolor='#1f77b4', color='w')
        axii.scatter(data, np.zeros_like(data), marker='x', 
                    c='k', label='Data', zorder=9)
        axii.plot(x, distribution.pdf(x), label='True pdf', c='r', ls='--')
        axii.set_title('bins = {}'.format(bi), size=24)
        axii.legend(loc='best');

                  [0.8,0.7,0.2],[0.7,-0.8,-0.45],[-0.3, 0.6, 0.9],

for row in X_inside:
    ax.scatter(row[0], row[1], row[2], color="r", s=50, marker='^')

for row in X_outside:
    ax.scatter(row[0], row[1], row[2], color="k", s=50)

# Plot Cube
h = [-0.5, 0.5]
for s, e in combinations(np.array(list(product(h,h,h))), 2):
    if np.sum(np.abs(s-e)) == h[1]-h[0]:
        ax.plot3D(*zip(s,e), color="g")

ax.set_xlim(-1.5, 1.5)
ax.set_ylim(-1.5, 1.5)
ax.set_zlim(-1.5, 1.5)

plt.show()

for bwmethod,t in zip([gde_01, gde_5, gde_20],[0.05, 0.5, 2]):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(22, 7))
    ax = fig.gca(projection='3d')
    Z = bwmethod(np.array([X.ravel(),Y.ravel()]))
    Z = Z.reshape(100,100)
    surf = ax.plot_surface(X, Y, Z, rstride=1, cstride=1, cmap=plt.cm.coolwarm,
        linewidth=0, antialiased=False)

    ax.set_zlim(0, 0.2)
    ax.zaxis.set_major_locator(plt.LinearLocator(10))
    ax.zaxis.set_major_formatter(plt.FormatStrFormatter('%.02f'))
    ax.set_xlabel('X')
    ax.set_ylabel('Y')
    ax.set_zlabel('p(x)')

    plt.title('Gaussian kernel, window width h={}'.format(t),size=20)
    fig.colorbar(surf, shrink=0.5, aspect=7, cmap=plt.cm.winter)
    plt.show()

In [30]:
class KNNClassifier(object):
    
    def __init__(self):
        pass
    
    def fit(self, X,y):
        self.X = X
        self.y = y
        self.labels = {tuple(X[i,:]):y[i] for i in range(y.shape[0])}
        
    def predict(self, Xnew, k=3):
        #each of the k nearest neighbors vote.
        ynew= zeros(Xnew.shape[0])
        for i,xi in enumerate(Xnew):
            # k nearest neighbors 
            slist = sorted(self.X, key=lambda x: np.linalg.norm(x-xi))[0:k] 
            preds = [self.labels[tuple(datapoint)] for datapoint in slist]
            ynew[i] = mode(preds, axis=None)[0]
        return ynew

#plotting code
def plot_contour_scatter(model, title_text, k=3,interval=0.1):
    #sample from a lattice (for the nice visualization)
    x1, x2 = meshgrid(arange(-5,5,interval), arange(-5,5,interval))
    Xnew = vstack((x1.ravel(), x2.ravel())).T

    Z = model.predict(Xnew, k=k).reshape((-1,1))

    #plot - contour plot and scatter superimposed
    contourf(arange(-5,5,interval), arange(-5,5,interval), Z[:,0].reshape(x1.shape),cmap ='summer',levels=arange(-0.1,1.1,0.05))
    colorsToUse=  ['r' if y[i] == 1 else 'b' for i in range(y.shape[0])]
    scatter(X[:,0],X[:,1], c=colorsToUse)
    title(title_text)
    show()
